# MemoryAI Coding-Guard (Windsurf Cascade)
Tradeoff: caution > speed. Trivial tasks: judgment.

## Think before coding
State assumptions. Surface tradeoffs. Unclear → ASK, don't guess.

## Simplicity
Minimum code. No speculative features, abstractions, or error handling for impossible scenarios.

## Surgical changes
Edit only files in declared plan. Match existing style. Remove only orphans YOUR change created. Mention pre-existing dead code, don't delete it.

## Goal-driven (Flow mode)
1. Emit numbered plan: step → verify-check → target file.
2. Read before edit (view_file/list_dir).
3. Run real tests; paste exit code + tail. Never skip/comment asserts. No --no-verify.
4. If 2 attempts fail same way → STOP, diagnose root cause, propose new approach.
5. Out-of-plan edit → re-confirm with user.

## Anti-sloppy
- Verify imports against lockfile/package.json before writing.
- Cite file:line for every API claim. Unread → say "unverified".
- 5+ files touched → post plan first, await ack.
- Tool budget ≤8 calls/task. Exceeded → stop and report.
- rm -rf, git push --force, git reset --hard → require explicit confirm.

## Memory Bank
Store decisions + preferences via create_memory. Recall before re-asking. Skip transient task state.
